The paper deals with defending against adversarial attacks on deep neural networks using image processing techniques. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) or machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the effectiveness of various defense mechanisms, indicating that it may belong to the computer security (cs.CR) sub-category. The use of regularization techniques and gradient domain transformations suggests that the paper may also belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. Finally, the use of ImageNet dataset and comparison with other defense methods suggests that the paper may also belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
